Defendant Joshua J. Paff in court with attorney Wright C. Laufenberg.  Defendant Joshua J. Paff in custody.  Galen Bayne-Allison appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court calls 15CF18, 15CF49, 15CF50, 15CF94, and 16CF5 @ 9:02 a.m. Agreement stated 15CF49 Def will plead to ct 1, 15CF50 plead to ct 1, 16CF5 plead to cts 1 & 2.  State will dismiss and read in remaining cts and also 15CF18 and 15CF94 in entirety. 15CF49 ct 1 - 15 days jail consecutive to any other sentence currently serving, 15CF50 ct 1 - 6 months jail, consecutive to all other sentences, 16CF5 cts 1 & 2, withheld sentence, 4 yrs probation. Atty Laufenberg and Def agree. Plea quest reviewed. 15CF49 ct 1 - no contest plea. 15CF50 ct 1 - no contest. 16CF5 cts 1 & 2 - no contest pleas. Court grants motion to dismiss and read in 15CF18 cts 1 & 2 and 15CF49 cts 2-5, 15CF50 cts 2 & 3. 15CF94 State has complied with VWNR, cts 1-7 dismissed and read in. Constitutional rights, elements, possible penalties reviewed. Atty Laufenberg satisfied. Court finds Def understands and pleas freely & voluntarily made. Factual basis. Court accepts pleas and finds Def guilty of 15CF49 ct 1 disorderly conduct, 15CF50 ct 1 throw/discharge bodily fluid at public safety worker, 16CF5 cts 1 & 2, throw/discharge bodily fluid at public safety worker, as repeater. Sentencing remarks by Counsel. Nothing by Defendant. Sentencing remarks by the Court. Statement by Defendant. Court approves agreement. 15CF49 ct 1 - 15 days jail, consecutive to all other sentences, court costs, including DNA surcharge. Any credit for time served will be determined, Court will hold open. Discussion regarding bonds, Court explains to poster. Court orders bonds returned to poster. 15CF50 ct 1 - 6 months jail, consecutive to all other sentences, court costs, including DNA surcharge. No credit ordered, but held open. Eligible for earned release and challenge inc. programs. Def advised of firearms and voting restrictions. 16CF5 ct 1 - sentence withheld, 4 yrs probation, court costs, DNA surcharge. Ct 2 - sentence withheld, 4 yrs probation, concurrent, court costs, DNA surcharge. No credit ordered at this time, but held open. Postconviction rights. 15CF49 & 50 - pp, Def to contact COC as soon as released.
